The nearly month-long conflict in Ukraine is having knock-on effects, and people in the rest of the world are feeling the consequences. What are the worst-affected sectors? And how is the use of economic weapons re-shaping thinking in this modern war? To look at the wider economic impact of the ongoing Ukraine crisis, we've invited Wang Dan, chief economist of Hang Seng Bank (China); Dr. William Lee, chief economist of the Milken Institute; and Andy Mok, senior research fellow at the Center for China and Globalization.